======================================================================
Z₂ CONSTRAINTS FOR PURE TT
======================================================================

For a TT path (a,b,c) with a→b→c, a→c:
  ∂₂(a,b,c) = (b,c) - (a,c) + (a,b)
  All three are edges in A₁.
  For z = Σ α_{abc} (a,b,c) ∈ Z₂: Σ α_{abc} ∂₂(a,b,c) = 0 in Ω₁
  This means: for each edge (i,j) ∈ A₁:
    Σ_{c: (i,j,c) TT} α_{ijc} - Σ_{a: (a,i,j) TT} α_{aij} + Σ_{b: (i,b,j) TT} α_{ibj} = 0

  Correct constraint for edge (i,j):
    Σ_a α_{a,i,j} - Σ_b α_{i,b,j} + Σ_c α_{i,j,c} = 0
    (sum over TT paths ending at ij) - (sum over TT paths with ij at ends) + (sum over TT paths starting at ij)

  Transitive T₅: 10 TT paths out of 10 allowed 2-paths
  Regular T₅: 5 TT, 15 NT out of 20 allowed 2-paths

Done.
